Description: Hello Everyone: What I have available is a 2013-2014 Fender Lone Star Stratocaster, It is Made in Mexico, It has the HSS setup, it has had the following changes done to it, a WD white Pearloid pickguard and tremolo cover were installed, Fender / Schaller Strap lock buttons installed, A Seymour Duncan SH16 humbucker installed, Fender black plastic parts installed, S1 knob, tone knobs and black pickup covers, other than this, the guitar is stock, the guitar has a factory S1 switch installed and Texas Special in the neck and middle positions factory installed, A Seymour Duncan Sh16 in the bridge with the S1 acting as a coil tap, the Guitar is in great shape, there is no dings, no dents, and no chips, the only flaw I see is on the back where you can see a line in the body under the finish, there is some light surface scratches from playing that could be easily polished out, all of the paperwork is included, and the whammy bar is included as well, also included is a black tip for the whammy bar, there is a white tip on it at the moment, the original gig bag is included, but it shows some wear from use, This lot is sold as is, Any questions?, please ask prior to bidding, Payment from the winning bidder should be received within 5 days end of auction, Thank you for looking and good luck bidding.
